      "Maybe it's better to loop back to this proposal:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nquery.nth(0).default(null)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat just isn't intuitive to me, but something like this would be reasonable IMO:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nquery.exists( function( error, exists ) {\r\n  // error if there's a db problem of some kind\r\n  // exists == true if the query matched at least one document, false otherwise\r\n} );\r\n```\r\n\r\nInternally, exists could just be the query.nth(0).default(null) implementation mentioned above, but a .exists() feels way more intuitive for end users to me."
